genresAdvancedInfo.name: musica ayacuchana
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Originating from the Andean region of Peru, Musica Ayacuchana is a traditional genre that incorporates indigenous instruments such as the charango and quena. It often tells stories of rural life and the struggles of the Andean people, with themes of love, loss, and social justice.
